The mean \(\mu = 0.25\) and the variance \(\sigma^2 = p(1-p)/n = (0.25)(0.75)/500 = 0.000375\). The standard deviation is \(\sigma = \sqrt{0.000375}\). The deviation \(d = 0.05\), so \(k = d / \sigma = 0.05 / \sqrt{0.000375} = 2\sqrt{5/3}\), and \(k^2 = 20/3\). Thus, \(1/k^2 = 3/20 = 0.15\).

