\[
E_{\text{photon}} = \frac{(6.626 \times 10^{-34}) \times (3.00 \times 10^8)}{3.00 \times 10^{-7}} = 6.626 \times 10^{-19}  \text{J}.
\]
For one mole of photons, multiply by Avogadro's number \( N_A = 6.022 \times 10^{23}  \text{mol}^{-1} \):
\[
E_{\text{mol}} = (6.626 \times 10^{-19}) \times (6.022 \times 10^{23}) = 3.990 \times 10^5  \text{J/mol} = 399  \text{kJ/mol}.
\]
The result is rounded to three significant figures based on the input wavelength of 300 nm.

